EnergyInjection README

This FLASH problem sets up a uniform gas distribution.
No particles are created - user should make particles via AMUSE interface.

The flash.par files can be treated as "suggestions" for what wind bubble / H II
region setups to run.  See also:
* bacyznski 2015 https://ui.adsabs.harvard.edu/abs/2015MNRAS.454..380B/abstract
* bisbas 2015 https://ui.adsabs.harvard.edu/abs/2015MNRAS.453.1324B/abstract

For example,

    $ diff -wbBu flash.par_dtype flash.par_rtype

shows that the "rtype" parameter file uses a 10x hotter and 10x less dense
ambient medium, and sim_Eph = 0 (make all ionizing photons contribute no extra
heat beyond the ionization potential 13.6 eV, they simply ionize gas).

Two big caveats:

1. Many parameters might not work or might be outdated.  E.g., sim_Eph was
   previously used to setup the single star in FLASH, but because we make the
   star in AMUSE now, sim_Eph should have no effect whatsoever.

2. I have not used these parameter files myself, so can't promise that
   flash.par_rtype will actually give you an R-type ionization front...

It's probably easier to start with the officially-maintained torch parameter
file flash.par.turbsph_standard , and make your own setups for different wind
bubbles / H II regions.  But these old files are here for reference should you
need/want to cross-check your parameter choices.

Provenance for this directory:

    https://bitbucket.org/joshuawall/flash4.2.2-rad/src/master/source/Simulation/SimulationMain/EnergyInjUSM/
    https://bitbucket.org/joshuawall/flash4.2.2-rad/commits/d746ac64

- Aaron Tran, 2020 Jan 15
